olive oil
1 bunch spring onion
½ fresh chilli
1 packet sugar snap peas
1 bunch mint
1 packet Japanese Dressing
1 tsp rice wine vinegar
½ tsp soy sauce
1 bag slaw mix
1 packet roasted peanuts

Thinly slice the spring onion and long red chilli (if using). Trim and thinly slice the sugar snap peas lengthways. Pick and thinly slice the mint leaves.

In a medium bowl, combine the Japanese dressing, rice wine vinegar, soy sauce and a drizzle of olive oil.

Add the slaw mix, spring onion and sugar snap peas to the dressing and toss to combine.

Transfer the Asian sugar snap pea slaw to a serving plate. Top with the roasted peanuts, mint and chilli (if using).